# Codegen And Generated Output Quality

Generated files under `packages/extension/demos/generated/tools/` must be **lint- and typecheck-clean without ESLint `--fix`**. Fix the generator templates, not the committed output.

**Always:** do not hand-edit `packages/extension/demos/generated/**` or bundled MCP files to fix behavior — see [generated-output-do-not-edit.mdc](./generated-output-do-not-edit.mdc).

## When this applies

Changes under `packages/cli/src/generator/` (or other generator wiring that affects `*-tools.ts` output).

## Required verification

From the **db2ai workspace root**, run in order:

1. `npm run build`
2. `npm run generate:all`
3. `npm run check:generated`

Do **not** run `eslint --fix` on generated files to “repair” output. If `check:generated` fails, fix the generator and regenerate.

## What `check:generated` covers

- `npm run lint:generated` — ESLint on committed `packages/extension/demos/generated/tools/**/*.ts` (no auto-fix)
- `npm run typecheck:generated` — `tsc -p packages/extension/demos/tsconfig.generated.json`

## Prettier only at generate time

The generator may run Prettier (`formatGeneratedFilesWithPrettier`) so output matches repo formatting. ESLint/type errors must be resolved in generator source, not patched after the fact.

## Commit generated output

When demo `.db2ai` files or generator output shape change, include regenerated `packages/extension/demos/generated/tools/*.ts` (and `.mjs` if changed) in the same change set.
